gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 138, Warriors 136
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Warriors, 138-136, in overtime. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander recorded 38 points, five rebounds, and five assists for the Thunder, with Jalen Williams adding 28 points and five rebounds in the victory. Stephen Curry tallied 34 points, six rebounds, and three assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Thunder improve to 14-7 in the regular season, while the Warriors fall to 10-12.
